FBIS3-9973 "drlat039_o_94009" FBIS-LAT-94-039 Document Type:Daily Report 28 Feb 1994 Colombia Energy Minister Announces Plan To Sell Oil to Cuba PA2502145994 Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network in Spanish 1200 GMT 25 Feb 94 PA2502145994 Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [From "Caracol's 0600 to 0900" newscast] [Text] Pereira -- Mines and Energy Minister Guido Alberto Nule Amin has announced here that Colombia will sell Cuba from 15,000 to 20,000 barrels of oil daily beginning in July and for an indefinite period under normal commercial conditions and without any privileges. [Begin Nule Amin recording] There are many things, mainly oil.... [pauses] there is interest in selling oil directly to Cuba. Cuba is interested in buying it under normal commercial conditions, naturally, under international conditions without any special considerations [words indistinct] very important that has to do with mining development in general. [end recording] The official added that in a few weeks, he will return to the island to complete the details of the oil negotiations.
